Interface ObjectView<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of objects stored in the view.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Items, Keys, Values
    public interface ObjectView<T>
    The ObjectView interface represents an object view in Python. It provides methods for interacting with the view of objects stored in a data structure, allowing for length retrieval, containment checks, iteration, and reverse iteration.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      boolean contains​(T other)
      Checks whether the specified element is contained in the object view.
      java.util.Iterator<T> iterator()
      Returns an iterator over the elements of the object view.
      int length()
      Returns the length of the object view, which corresponds to the number of elements in the view.
      java.lang.Iterable<T> reversed()
      Returns an iterable object that allows reverse iteration over the elements of the object view.

    • Method Detail

      • length

        int length()
        Returns the length of the object view, which corresponds to the number of elements in the view.
        Returns:
        The length of the object view.

      • contains

        boolean contains​(T other)
        Checks whether the specified element is contained in the object view.
        Parameters:
        other - The element to check for containment.
        Returns:
        True if the element is contained in the object view, false otherwise.

      • iterator

        java.util.Iterator<T> iterator()
        Returns an iterator over the elements of the object view. Iteration should be performed in the same order as the elements are stored in the object that is viewed.
        Returns:
        An iterator over the elements of the object view.

      • reversed

        java.lang.Iterable<T> reversed()
        Returns an iterable object that allows reverse iteration over the elements of the object view. Reverse iteration should be performed in the opposite order as the elements are stored in the object that is viewed.
        Returns:
        An iterable object for reverse iteration over the elements of the object view.
